He Zhi Nan, wake up.

4
00:01:53,359 --> 00:01:54,400
He Zhi Nan.

5
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:57,079
Your wage is going to be deducted.

6
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:58,640
He Zhi Nan.

7
00:01:59,079 --> 00:02:00,159
He Zhi Nan.

8
00:02:04,519 --> 00:02:05,680
He Zhi Nan.

9
00:02:24,090 --> 00:02:25,479
- Morning, Han Han. - Morning.

10
00:02:35,090 --> 00:02:36,240
- Morning. - Morning.

11
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,400
Good morning.

12
00:02:40,759 --> 00:02:41,810
Morning.

13
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:46,879
Han Su, let me tell you something.

14
00:02:47,439 --> 00:02:48,679
I just heard...

15
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:50,680
that the Hong Kong branch is asking for someone.

16
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:51,999
Really?

17
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,376
After the meeting earlier, the district lawyer Mr. Wu...

18
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:55,719
asked Ms. Xu if she has a suitable candidate.

19
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,079
What did Ms. Xu say?

20
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:58,758
She told him not to worry.

21
00:02:58,759 --> 00:03:00,599
It seems like she already has someone in mind.

22
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,520
You're so quick to find out.

23
00:03:18,479 --> 00:03:20,999
When filling out the intention survey for HR,

24
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,439
that was what I applied for.

25
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,799
Job opportunities in Hong Kong...

26
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,479
are very attractive to everyone.

27
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:29,799
But I have to remind you...

28
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:31,480
that you just became a second-year lawyer.

29
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,758
The work environment in Hong Kong...

30
00:03:33,759 --> 00:03:35,439
is too stressful...

31
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:37,639
for a junior lawyer.

32
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:40,280
Why don't you practice in a familiar environment...

33
00:03:40,639 --> 00:03:41,759
for another two years...

34
00:03:42,199 --> 00:03:43,479
before you go there?

35
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:44,918
Of course,

36
00:03:44,919 --> 00:03:47,479
the income in Hong Kong is much higher.

37
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:49,960
But the cost of living will also be higher.

38
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,079
Thank you, Ms. Xu.

39
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:53,360
You're very thoughtful.

40
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,280
But if it's possible,

41
00:03:55,479 --> 00:03:56,959
I'd still like to seize the opportunity...

42
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:57,960
to work in Hong Kong.

43
00:03:59,159 --> 00:04:00,439
Is there a personal reason?

44
00:04:04,159 --> 00:04:05,400
I'll be honest with you.

45
00:04:06,199 --> 00:04:07,879
The company already has someone in mind.

46
00:04:08,719 --> 00:04:10,198
There's also the language barrier issue.

47
00:04:10,199 --> 00:04:11,280
That's not a problem.

48
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,520
I've been learning Cantonese on my own for a year.

49
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:16,169
I just hope that the company...

50
00:04:16,170 --> 00:04:18,199
will give me a fair chance to compete.

51
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:24,759
You came prepared.

52
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:30,639
Okay.

53
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:31,800
If you insist.

54
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,519
Go and prepare the application.

55
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:37,730
But you have to know that the final decision...

56
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,519
is with the major partner in Hong Kong.

57
00:04:39,610 --> 00:04:40,959
Thank you, Ms. Xu.

58
00:04:42,839 --> 00:04:43,839
Han Su.

59
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,730
I'm just curious.

60
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:49,520
You'll have to spend three years in Hong Kong.

61
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,120
What about your Handsome Qu?

62
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,120
Can you bear to part with him?

63
00:04:54,639 --> 00:04:56,050
He'll definitely support me.

64
00:04:57,399 --> 00:04:58,439
That's good.

65
00:05:12,519 --> 00:05:13,560
Let me see.

66
00:05:15,610 --> 00:05:16,639
Hi.

67
00:05:17,959 --> 00:05:19,279
Xiao Peng.

68
00:05:21,759 --> 00:05:23,656
I sent you an article yesterday. Did you read it?

69
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,730
I did.

70
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:26,169
It's still early for the meeting.

71
00:05:26,170 --> 00:05:28,479
Why don't we go to my office? I want to hear your thoughts.

72
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:29,720
- Let's go. - Okay.

73
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,198
Miss.

74
00:05:33,199 --> 00:05:34,600
The client hasn't signed in.

75
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:36,638
Mr. Qu is my friend from Yinzhong Capital.

76
00:05:36,639 --> 00:05:37,920
Just check the box.

77
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:41,319
Don't you think...

78
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:43,278
Ms. J is the type of mistress...

79
00:05:43,279 --> 00:05:45,159
coming from a poor background...

80
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:47,720
who is desperately climbing up the social ladder in telenovelas?

81
00:05:49,839 --> 00:05:52,319
Have you fallen for the handsome guy?

82
00:05:53,199 --> 00:05:55,480
I do like idol dramas, but I'm not stupid.

83
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:57,958
These high achievers...

84
00:05:57,959 --> 00:05:59,800
are mostly from small cities.

85
00:05:59,839 --> 00:06:01,399
They want to settle down in a big city.

86
00:06:01,879 --> 00:06:04,439
At a time like this, Ms. J has the money and resources.

87
00:06:04,680 --> 00:06:06,016
She definitely has more advantages...

88
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:08,040
than innocent, young, and pretty girls.

89
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,800
And Ms. J won't force him to get married.

90
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,198
He can have a romantic relationship with an independent older woman...

91
00:06:13,199 --> 00:06:14,278
and not take responsibility.

92
00:06:14,279 --> 00:06:15,519
Why not?

93
00:06:15,879 --> 00:06:16,959
Hello.

94
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:18,160
What's your name?

95
00:06:20,639 --> 00:06:22,360
Hello. What's your name?

96
00:06:27,279 --> 00:06:28,600
Let me check. Excuse me.

97
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:31,295
(Qu Yi Peng: I couldn't say hi to you earlier.)

98
00:06:31,319 --> 00:06:32,919
(Let me thank you for saving me a seat.)

99
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:42,120
(It's nothing. Don't mention it.)

100
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,278
It's the handsome guy from the food stall.

101
00:06:53,279 --> 00:06:55,759
A lot of girls in our office think he's handsome.

102
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:57,560
They shared his photos in the group chat.

103
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,079
They said he looks like Xin Yunlai.

104
00:07:00,279 --> 00:07:01,479
How can he be compared to him?

105
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,119
I say, aesthetics have been downgraded.

106
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,999
I think he's quite handsome.

107
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,360
Coupled with the label of a famous company finance man,

108
00:07:07,439 --> 00:07:08,560
he's of top-notch quality.

109
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,800
Creativity means competitiveness.

110
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:19,120
It also means facing the unknown.

111
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:22,560
Compared to being fearless,

112
00:07:22,839 --> 00:07:24,079
I enjoy...

113
00:07:24,279 --> 00:07:26,119
facing the fear and doubt of the unknown more.

114
00:07:26,759 --> 00:07:27,920
You're only eating lunch now?

115
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:30,559
I just finished the final summary...

116
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,800
of the Melon Seed King project.

117
00:07:34,439 --> 00:07:36,318
Golden Harvest is such a big award in advertising.

118
00:07:36,319 --> 00:07:38,919
Even winning it once, I'll be satisfied for life.

119
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,159
Ms. Zeng has won it three times.

120
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:41,160
She's immune to it.

121
00:07:41,161 --> 00:07:42,479
She's amazing.

122
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:44,599
When I'm out of ideas, I listen to her lecture.

123
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,000
I always learn something out of it.

124
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:47,759
Next time,

125
00:07:47,839 --> 00:07:49,599
I should invite her to the company...

126
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:51,040
to give us a seminar.

127
00:07:51,319 --> 00:07:52,319
Ms. Xin.

128
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:54,198
Do you know Ms. Zeng well?

129
00:07:54,199 --> 00:07:56,399
She's kind of my mentor.

130
00:07:57,959 --> 00:07:59,040
I see.

131
00:07:59,079 --> 00:08:00,159
This is what they call...

132
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:01,720
a good teacher produces a good student.

133
00:08:01,879 --> 00:08:03,959
When did you learn how to suck up to others?

134
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,079
But to be honest,

135
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:07,638
Ms. Zeng is really amazing.

136
00:08:07,639 --> 00:08:09,438
No matter how difficult and boring a project is,

137
00:08:09,439 --> 00:08:11,639
it's always something new in her hands.

138
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:14,360
Her way of thinking and execution...

139
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,760
is just different from others.

140
00:08:21,279 --> 00:08:22,878
Hi, my babies.

141
00:08:22,879 --> 00:08:23,959
I'm back.

142
00:08:24,199 --> 00:08:26,039
- Monica. - Monica.

143
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,079
You're finally back.

144
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:28,919
Long time no see. Come.

145
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,758
I came back today...

146
00:08:30,759 --> 00:08:32,329
to give out wedding candies.

147
00:08:32,330 --> 00:08:33,855
It's like I'm back visiting my parents.

148
00:08:33,879 --> 00:08:35,798
- Congratulations. - Congratulations, Monica.

149
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:37,799
She just did one project with you...

150
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:40,279
and turned your client into her husband.

151
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,799
I'll go out first.

152
00:08:45,159 --> 00:08:46,599
I brought everything. Hand them out.

153
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,360
Monica.

154
00:08:49,361 --> 00:08:50,879
It has been a while.

155
00:08:50,919 --> 00:08:51,919
Ms. Xin.

156
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:55,449
I didn't expect you to get married so soon.

157
00:08:55,450 --> 00:08:57,050
- Congratulations. - Thank you, Ms. Xin.

158
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,239
Here, this is for you.

159
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:00,758
- Thank you. - Come this way.

160
00:09:00,759 --> 00:09:02,360
- So how are you? - Pretty good.

161
00:09:03,279 --> 00:09:04,279
It's my fault.

162
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:06,120
I've loved Norse mythology since I was little.

163
00:09:06,279 --> 00:09:08,240
To fulfil my dream, Sun took the whole family...

164
00:09:08,450 --> 00:09:10,960
to a Nordic castle to hold the wedding.

165
00:09:11,559 --> 00:09:13,918
Time was tight too. It was really tiring.

166
00:09:13,919 --> 00:09:15,758
Your husband is so good to you.

167
00:09:15,759 --> 00:09:16,919
He's all right.

168
00:09:17,279 --> 00:09:18,638
I just got back last week.,

169
00:09:18,639 --> 00:09:19,960
so I'm still jet-lagged.

170
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,210
But I wanted to see everyone.

171
00:09:21,679 --> 00:09:22,999
- It must be tough. - Monica.

172
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,639
Congratulations on your wedding.

173
00:09:24,879 --> 00:09:26,759
Han Han, this is for you.

174
00:09:27,210 --> 00:09:28,240
Thank you.

175
00:09:28,519 --> 00:09:29,799
I haven't thanked you properly.

176
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:31,600
What for?

177
00:09:31,679 --> 00:09:33,119
In my heart,

178
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:35,159
I regard you as my matchmaker.

179
00:09:35,639 --> 00:09:37,209
If you didn't take me on the project,

180
00:09:37,210 --> 00:09:38,919
I wouldn't have met Sun.

181
00:09:41,039 --> 00:09:42,798
Mrs. Sun, congratulations.

182
00:09:42,799 --> 00:09:44,918
Mr. Li, please don't call me that.

183
00:09:44,919 --> 00:09:46,090
Just call me Monica.

184
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,918
Very well. May you have children soon.

185
00:09:47,919 --> 00:09:49,000
Thank you, Mr. Li.

186
00:09:49,210 --> 00:09:51,449
During the economic transformation,

187
00:09:51,450 --> 00:09:52,558
China's macroeconomy...

188
00:09:52,559 --> 00:09:54,519
has generally maintained a rapid growth.

189
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:56,558
A large group of outstanding entrepreneurs...

190
00:09:56,559 --> 00:09:57,799
stood out from the crowd.

191
00:09:58,039 --> 00:09:59,329
Countless small businesses...

192
00:09:59,330 --> 00:10:01,759
have grown into modern mega conglomerates.

193
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:02,960
However,

194
00:10:02,961 --> 00:10:05,799
many companies were also affected...

195
00:10:06,210 --> 00:10:09,239
by economic cycle fluctuations at the macro-level...

196
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:10,360
during their growth process.

197
00:10:10,559 --> 00:10:12,329
Or they couldn't adapt...

198
00:10:12,330 --> 00:10:14,209
to the requirements of economic development...

199
00:10:14,210 --> 00:10:15,638
and the demand for industrial upgrades...

200
00:10:15,639 --> 00:10:16,919
on a micro-level.

201
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,158
Or perhaps...

202
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:20,089
there were financial crises due to illegal operations...

203
00:10:20,090 --> 00:10:21,399
and so on.

204
00:10:22,639 --> 00:10:24,449
The competition mechanism under market economy conditions...

205
00:10:24,450 --> 00:10:26,398
has caused some corporations in the entire economic system...

206
00:10:26,399 --> 00:10:28,450
to put on a comedy show,

207
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:29,680
while other corporations...

208
00:10:29,759 --> 00:10:31,000
put on tragedies.

209
00:10:31,399 --> 00:10:33,479
What's more, some corporations...

210
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:36,159
have become a confluence of comedy and tragedy.

211
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:37,798
Without a doubt, Delong Group...

212
00:10:37,799 --> 00:10:40,120
has become a typical example of this confluence.

213
00:10:40,559 --> 00:10:42,135
(Qu Yi Peng: Zhi Nan, you have to help me.)

214
00:10:42,159 --> 00:10:43,450
(A girl keeps pestering me.)

215
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,816
(If you don't agree to meet with me tonight, I...)

216
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:48,089
Delong Group was a small colour photo enlargement shop...

217
00:10:48,090 --> 00:10:49,600
registered in Urumqi...

218
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:52,450
in 1986 with 400 employees.

219
00:10:53,039 --> 00:10:54,678
After 18 years of development,

220
00:10:54,679 --> 00:10:55,758
in 2004,

221
00:10:55,759 --> 00:10:57,440
the company has developed...

222
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:00,158
into a multipurpose, multi-industry,

223
00:11:00,159 --> 00:11:02,200
multiregional, and multinational company.

224
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:18,320
Sorry.

225
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,679
I rushed, but I'm still late.

226
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:24,279
I'm sorry.

227
00:11:24,559 --> 00:11:25,600
It's okay.

228
00:11:27,519 --> 00:11:28,559
Thank you.

229
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:35,960
Ms. J just wouldn't believe that I had an appointment.

230
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:38,600
I even showed her the message of the restaurant's location.

231
00:11:38,639 --> 00:11:39,798
She still didn't believe me.

232
00:11:39,799 --> 00:11:42,158
She even insisted on driving me to the restaurant.

233
00:11:42,159 --> 00:11:43,399
That's when she gave up.

234
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:47,360
Ms. J likes handsome guys from prestigious schools.

235
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:50,239
"Handsome guys from prestigious schools"?

236
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:51,759
Do you think I'm one too?

237
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:55,799
He's so good at flirting.

238
00:12:01,639 --> 00:12:04,919
Actually, it's not just about looks.

239
00:12:05,559 --> 00:12:06,559
Education too.

240
00:12:06,759 --> 00:12:08,079
He must be from a prestigious local university.

241
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:09,558
Since it has to be a prestigious school,

242
00:12:09,559 --> 00:12:12,440
then are Ivy League schools within her consideration?

243
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,279
To be able to go to an Ivy League school,

244
00:12:15,639 --> 00:12:16,799
then his family must be rich.

245
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:19,040
She doesn't care about having a rich lady image.

246
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,080
Is that so?

247
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:24,880
Take a look at what you want to eat.

248
00:12:29,799 --> 00:12:32,440
I chose this Western restaurant without knowing what you like.

249
00:12:32,879 --> 00:12:34,120
By the way, where are you from?

250
00:12:35,279 --> 00:12:37,120
I'm from here. I can eat anything.

251
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:41,200
Being a local kid is lucky.

252
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:44,960
When it comes to rent, it's a lot less stressful.

253
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:46,720
Do you live with your parents?

254
00:12:46,799 --> 00:12:47,919
I live alone.

255
00:12:49,559 --> 00:12:51,559
My parents bought me a house.

256
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:54,799
How nice.

257
00:12:56,679 --> 00:12:59,080
Unlike us from out of town.

258
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:01,080
We have worked hard for years,

259
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:03,279
but buying a house isn't considered.

260
00:13:05,519 --> 00:13:06,639
Can I take your order?

261
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:12,279
Perilla pasta.

262
00:13:13,279 --> 00:13:15,679
Caesar salad. Freshly squeezed watermelon juice.

263
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:17,720
And tiramisu. Thank you.

264
00:13:19,039 --> 00:13:22,039
I'll have a grilled chicken breast salad.

265
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:25,000
And a bottle of this red wine.

266
00:13:25,639 --> 00:13:26,960
- Okay. - Thank you.

267
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:32,799
Is he on a diet?

268
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,560
Or is he trying to humiliate you?

269
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:40,278
Don't get me wrong.

270
00:13:40,279 --> 00:13:41,679
I'm doing this to complement you.

271
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:44,039
You eat so much, but you're still so skinny.

272
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,760
You must be the envy of so many girls.

273
00:13:49,279 --> 00:13:50,599
It must be nice to be young.

274
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:52,678
An old man like me...

275
00:13:52,679 --> 00:13:54,559
has to control his calorie intake.

276
00:13:54,679 --> 00:13:56,279
