That was all.

554
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:44,439
Other than that,

555
00:34:44,440 --> 00:34:46,638
she never taught me anything valuable.

556
00:34:46,639 --> 00:34:49,199
So I don't think of her as my mentor.

557
00:34:49,289 --> 00:34:51,400
There are some things that only you need to know.

558
00:34:51,719 --> 00:34:53,159
Why do you have to say it in person?

559
00:34:53,679 --> 00:34:55,159
Because it's more efficient this way.

560
00:34:56,840 --> 00:34:59,158
I don't have to spend time greeting her and smiling at her,

561
00:34:59,159 --> 00:35:00,400
and beating around the bush.

562
00:35:00,480 --> 00:35:03,119
If so, it'll take at least 30 minutes.

563
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:05,360
I don't have that kind of time...

564
00:35:05,679 --> 00:35:07,199
nor the energy or ability...

565
00:35:07,480 --> 00:35:09,840
to delve into these office small talks.

566
00:35:10,039 --> 00:35:11,719
It's not that you don't have the energy...

567
00:35:11,769 --> 00:35:12,880
or the ability.

568
00:35:13,880 --> 00:35:15,400
You just don't care.

569
00:35:17,719 --> 00:35:18,769
Ms. Xu.

570
00:35:18,840 --> 00:35:20,479
I know you're reminding me this...

571
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:21,880
for my own good.

572
00:35:22,329 --> 00:35:23,440
I thank you.

573
00:35:24,719 --> 00:35:26,719
But you don't plan to change either.

574
00:35:26,809 --> 00:35:27,880
That's right.

575
00:35:32,880 --> 00:35:34,679
You're an honest person.

576
00:35:39,289 --> 00:35:40,840
Don't change if you don't want to.

577
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:43,288
I don't have the interest...

578
00:35:43,289 --> 00:35:44,960
or the energy to mediate anyway.

579
00:35:45,960 --> 00:35:47,200
From the perspective of a boss,

580
00:35:47,519 --> 00:35:48,559
I don't mind.

581
00:35:48,639 --> 00:35:49,718
As for the others,

582
00:35:49,719 --> 00:35:50,919
as long as you don't care about them,

583
00:35:50,920 --> 00:35:52,329
it doesn't matter.

584
00:35:52,809 --> 00:35:53,960
Thank you, Ms. Xu.

585
00:35:55,329 --> 00:35:57,000
People who stand up for themselves...

586
00:35:57,599 --> 00:36:01,329
tend to unconsciously build iron walls around themselves...

587
00:36:01,679 --> 00:36:02,809
for support.

588
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:06,399
As someone who has the experience,

589
00:36:06,400 --> 00:36:07,679
I want to remind you...

590
00:36:08,440 --> 00:36:09,880
that these iron walls...

591
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:12,880
can sometimes trap you instead.

592
00:36:14,599 --> 00:36:15,920
That feeling of loneliness...

593
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:17,559
is not pleasant.

594
00:37:26,809 --> 00:37:28,039
You're back.

595
00:37:29,639 --> 00:37:30,840
Have you eaten?

596
00:37:33,079 --> 00:37:34,440
Yes.

597
00:37:37,769 --> 00:37:40,480
Last week, I introduced you to my senior from Huineng Group.

598
00:37:41,239 --> 00:37:42,519
How did the meeting go?

599
00:37:45,719 --> 00:37:47,039
The project...

600
00:37:47,599 --> 00:37:48,599
hasn't been set yet.

601
00:37:49,199 --> 00:37:50,599
I don't think it's going to happen.

602
00:37:51,159 --> 00:37:53,400
Their company's lithium technology is state-of-the-art.

603
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:55,769
New energy source is the current trend.

604
00:37:57,159 --> 00:38:00,159
You can't just look at the surface.

605
00:38:00,639 --> 00:38:01,879
You have to put in some effort.

606
00:38:01,920 --> 00:38:03,359
Investigate properly...

607
00:38:03,360 --> 00:38:04,480
and research seriously.

608
00:38:05,840 --> 00:38:07,680
"Investigate properly and research seriously"?

609
00:38:07,880 --> 00:38:09,599
Why do you sound so much like my boss?

610
00:38:09,679 --> 00:38:11,679
He only sleeps five hours a day.

611
00:38:11,809 --> 00:38:14,599
He despises anyone who sleeps eight hours a day.

612
00:38:14,809 --> 00:38:15,809
We're doomed.

613
00:38:15,810 --> 00:38:17,930
He suspects us of slacking off in the office all day.

614
00:38:19,639 --> 00:38:22,769
The way you said that is exactly like...

615
00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:25,199
those old-timers in our company.

616
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:28,079
They can't do their job well.

617
00:38:28,920 --> 00:38:30,360
They're stuck in their comfort zone.

618
00:38:30,599 --> 00:38:32,809
Yet they mock people who work hard for being arrogant.

619
00:38:35,599 --> 00:38:37,039
What do you mean?

620
00:38:37,809 --> 00:38:38,920
I meant it literally.

621
00:38:47,159 --> 00:38:48,239
For the past two years,

622
00:38:49,519 --> 00:38:52,239
I've always heard you complaining about your boss.

623
00:38:53,079 --> 00:38:54,119
But...

624
00:38:54,159 --> 00:38:57,039
shouldn't you look for the reason in yourself?

625
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:01,289
From what you're saying,

626
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:03,808
you think I'm too slow to get promoted and get a raise.

627
00:39:03,809 --> 00:39:05,169
That's not what I'm talking about.

628
00:39:08,289 --> 00:39:09,400
Forget it.

629
00:39:30,960 --> 00:39:33,336
The lid of the pickled bamboo shoots jar is not closed properly.

630
00:39:33,360 --> 00:39:35,360
The smell won't get out for half a day.

631
00:39:42,079 --> 00:39:43,719
You don't like the smell?

632
00:39:45,639 --> 00:39:47,960
I just don't like the smell of always being in the house.

633
00:39:48,769 --> 00:39:50,769
This is the smell I've smelled since I was little.

634
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:52,559
My sister made it herself.

635
00:39:52,809 --> 00:39:54,399
I held it and rode the train for over ten hours...

636
00:39:54,400 --> 00:39:55,400
to bring it back.

637
00:39:56,679 --> 00:39:58,039
I'm just a country bumpkin...

638
00:39:58,119 --> 00:39:59,399
who made it to where I am today.

639
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:01,238
If I don't smell this for three days,

640
00:40:01,239 --> 00:40:02,439
I'll feel uncomfortable.

641
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:03,800
If you don't like it, just say so.

642
00:40:04,199 --> 00:40:05,289
Let's be objective.

643
00:40:05,840 --> 00:40:07,976
Not liking it and rejecting it are two different things.

644
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:09,119
Don't exaggerate.

645
00:40:09,199 --> 00:40:10,559
I'm exaggerating?

646
00:40:11,719 --> 00:40:13,480
The first time I made the noodles for you,

647
00:40:14,119 --> 00:40:15,440
you said it tasted heavenly.

648
00:40:16,719 --> 00:40:18,279
The taste of the noodles never changed.

649
00:40:18,719 --> 00:40:19,999
Could it be that you've changed?

650
00:40:20,719 --> 00:40:23,079
I loved it then and I still love it now.

651
00:40:23,159 --> 00:40:25,329
I just don't like the smell of the sour marinade.

652
00:40:25,599 --> 00:40:27,159
The ventilation in this house is bad.

653
00:40:27,329 --> 00:40:28,718
The smell can't get out. That's the truth.

654
00:40:28,719 --> 00:40:29,809
That's all.

655
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:33,160
I don't think the bamboo shoots are the problem, it's you.

656
00:40:34,440 --> 00:40:36,840
After all this talk, you finally got to the point.

657
00:40:37,039 --> 00:40:38,559
Yes, the problem is me.

658
00:40:39,920 --> 00:40:41,119
I'm from a poor background.

659
00:40:41,199 --> 00:40:42,480
And I don't work hard.

660
00:40:42,960 --> 00:40:45,159
When I don't finish my writing, I can still sleep.

661
00:40:45,329 --> 00:40:46,559
That's not progressing.

662
00:40:46,920 --> 00:40:47,960
That's a sin.

663
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:49,600
I stayed up all night for you.

664
00:40:50,400 --> 00:40:51,559
I didn't complain at all.

665
00:40:51,639 --> 00:40:52,719
Thank you, Han Su.

666
00:40:53,840 --> 00:40:54,920
You don't have to complain.

667
00:40:56,119 --> 00:40:57,289
What you said is true.

668
00:40:57,599 --> 00:40:59,920
I can't be as strong and hardworking as you, Superman Han.

669
00:41:00,239 --> 00:41:01,239
I deserve to be despised.

670
00:41:01,400 --> 00:41:03,360
You're trying so hard to hide your hatred,

671
00:41:03,519 --> 00:41:05,119
acting like you care about my pride.

672
00:41:05,599 --> 00:41:06,678
But let me tell you,

673
00:41:06,679 --> 00:41:08,215
it hurts more than just looking down on me.

674
00:41:08,239 --> 00:41:09,360
Qu Yi Peng, be fair.

675
00:41:09,840 --> 00:41:11,239
I just can't stand it...

676
00:41:11,289 --> 00:41:12,599
when you don't finish your work,

677
00:41:12,679 --> 00:41:13,920
but can still sleep peacefully.

678
00:41:14,329 --> 00:41:15,439
It's the truth...

679
00:41:15,440 --> 00:41:17,400
that I can't say out loud or not tell you either.

680
00:41:17,599 --> 00:41:18,679
What should I do?

681
00:41:18,960 --> 00:41:21,120
- What did I do wrong? - You didn't do anything wrong.

682
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:23,039
I'm the one at fault.

683
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:24,599
My existence is a mistake.

684
00:41:28,159 --> 00:41:29,360
I think you want to say...

685
00:41:30,400 --> 00:41:31,840
it's my existence that's a mistake.

686
00:41:33,159 --> 00:41:34,519
No. What do you mean?

687
00:42:06,639 --> 00:42:09,360
(Four-year anniversary, tomorrow)
